President Barack Obama released a statement praising Senator Barbara Boxer for her more than three decades of service to the people of California. He commended her for fighting for important issues such as clean air, clean water, healthcare access for women, after-school programs for children, and the protection of public lands. President Obama also highlighted Boxer's role as an inspiration for young women to achieve their dreams. He expressed his pleasure in working with her and noted that she works tirelessly for the people of California. While her retirement at the end of her term will be greatly missed, President Obama looks forward to continuing to work with her for the next two years.